Police say gunmen have kidnapped three teachers at the Dadaab refugee camp in eastern Kenya. JOHANNESBURG - Kenyan police say gunmen have kidnapped three teachers at the Dadaab refugee camp in eastern Kenya, which hosts more than 200,000 Somali refugees.Kenyan authorities said in May they would close the camp, claiming it had become a recruitment and training ground for Somalia s extremist group Al-Shabaab.But authorities have not provided proof of this claim.Al-Shabaab has carried out several attacks on Kenya, including the 2015 attack on the Garissa University in which 148 people were killed.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)